{
  "doc_id": "7603",
  "text": "From a pathophysiological point, migraine, RCVS and cervical artery dissection (CAD) are three distinct headache syndromes (ICHD-III) that might share more than just this main clinical symptom of headache. [CITATION_1] Mawet et al. performed a systematic review on this topic and found common and complex epidemiological, clinical and genetic features, which might explain their association. [CITATION_2] Our individual clinical case unifies all three headaches with an additional fourth (post-dural puncture headache) and supports this hypothesis clinically.",
